From: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 02:39:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 26/27] dt-bindings: mailbox: mediatek: add MT6797 GCE

MT6797 has the original 16-thread Global Command Engine register layout
with unshifted 32-bit command-buffer addresses. Add its compatible with the
MT8173 fallback and a complete header for the subsystem selectors and
hardware events exposed by this SoC.

The constants are recovered from the public MT6797 vendor device tree and
its CMDQ event/subsystem tables rather than copied from MT6795. The two
SoCs have substantially different display event numbering.

Signed-off-by: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
---
 .../bindings/mailbox/mediatek,gce-mailbox.yaml |   3 +
 .../dt-bindings/gce/mediatek,mt6797-gce.h      | 160 ++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 163 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/mailbox/mediatek,gce-mailbox.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/mailbox/mediatek,gce-mailbox.yaml
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/mailbox/mediatek,gce-mailbox.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/mailbox/mediatek,gce-mailbox.yaml
@@ -29,6 +29,9 @@ properties:
       - items:
           - const: mediatek,mt6795-gce
           - const: mediatek,mt8173-gce
+      - items:
+          - const: mediatek,mt6797-gce
+          - const: mediatek,mt8173-gce
 
   "#mbox-cells":
     const: 2
diff --git a/include/dt-bindings/gce/mediatek,mt6797-gce.h b/include/dt-bindings/gce/mediatek,mt6797-gce.h
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
